{"type":"message","id":"c0d06d56","parentId":"d0a784fb","timestamp":"2026-06-22T16:00:04.027Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[cron:500a1a24-2ac8-4b36-837a-43d940722302 Noticias IA y Temperatura Goicoechea] Crea un reporte matutino especializado para Kenneth (IA Engineer en formación). ENFOQUE: 1. TEMPERATURA de Goicoechea, CR. 2. NOTICIAS TÉCNICAS PARA IA ENGINEERS, con énfasis en: - Herramientas para desarrolladores full-stack (frontend + IA) - APIs y bibliotecas de IA para TypeScript/JavaScript - Integración de IA con frontend moderno (React, Vue, Tailwind) - Recursos de aprendizaje práctico para IA Engineering - Frameworks y herramientas accesibles para desarrolladores web 3. ANÁLISIO PRÁCTICO: Cómo aplicar las noticias en proyectos de aprendizaje. 4. RECOMENDACIÓN DIARIA: Una herramienta, tutorial o recurso para practicar. Formato: Breve, práctico, enfocado en aprendizaje activo.\nCurrent time: Monday, June 22nd, 2026 - 4:00 PM (UTC)\nReference UTC: 2026-06-22 16:00 UTC\n\nUse the message tool if you need to notify the user directly for the current chat. If you do not send directly, your final plain-text reply will be delivered automatically."}],"timestamp":1782144004024}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3232d6e","parentId":"c0d06d56","timestamp":"2026-06-22T16:00:14.489Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Voy a crear un reporte matutino especializado para Kenneth. Primero, necesito obtener la temperatura actual de Goicoechea, Costa Rica y las noticias técnicas más relevantes para IA Engineers"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"f746a934fda5408f82d96fee13f0d9ee","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","arguments":{"queries":[{"use_case":"get current weather for a specific location","known_fields":"location:Goicoechea, Costa Rica"},{"use_case":"search for latest AI developer tools and news for full-stack developers"}],"session":{"generate_id":true}},"partialArgs":"{\"queries\": [{\"use_case\": \"get current weather for a specific location\", \"known_fields\": \"location:Goicoechea, Costa Rica\"}, {\"use_case\": \"search for latest AI developer tools and news for full-stack developers\"}], \"session\": {\"generate_id\": true}}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782144004035,"responseId":"gen-1782144004-OwjSUV0C8JypTfa99la8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1284119f","parentId":"b3232d6e","timestamp":"2026-06-22T16:00:17.926Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"f746a934fda5408f82d96fee13f0d9ee","toolName":"composio__COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"data\":{\"results\":[{\"index\":1,\"use_case\":\"get current weather for a specific location\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Step]: Retrieve current conditions using WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (use the provided location text; present a clear place label and consistent display units).\",\"[Optional (if local-time labeling is needed)] [Step]: Use the returned timezone offset from WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (or a known offset) to label the observation in local time/day.\",\"[Optional (if the location text is ambiguous, not found, or results look mismatched)] [Prerequisite]: Disambiguate using WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION (select best candidate + canonical label), then re-run WEATHERMAP_WEATHER (same unit conventions).\",\"[Optional (if you need coordinate-based consistency and have an authenticated provider available)] [Prerequisite]: Resolve the location to coordinates using OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT (choose best regional match when multiple).\",\"[Optional (if using coordinates for current conditions)] [Step]: Retrieve current conditions using OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER (pass lat and lon separately; keep units aligned with WEATHERMAP_WEATHER output).\",\"[Optional (if a short multi-day forecast is requested)] [Next Step]: Retrieve intervals using OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST (summarize by local day using the returned timezone offset; report day min/max and prevailing conditions).\",\"[Fallback (if authenticated OpenWeather calls fail or are unavailable, e.g., HTTP 401)] [Fallback]: Use WEATHERMAP_WEATHER only and clearly label output as current conditions (no forecast).\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Response is typically nested under weather_info (and may be additionally wrapped); verify the path before indexing (e.g., weather_info.main.temp, weather_info.wind.speed).\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Temperatures may appear Kelvin-like; convert to the chosen display units before summarizing.\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] timezone is an offset in seconds (weather_info.timezone); apply it when labeling local time/day.\",\"[WEATHERMAP_WEATHER] Can return HTTP 404 for some formatted place strings; retry with a simpler string or geocode first via WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION.\",\"[OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER] HTTP 401 indicates invalid/missing credentials (non-retriable); also ensure lat and lon are provided as separate inputs.\"],\"reference_workbench_snippets\":[{\"description\":\"Compute local-day key from a UNIX timestamp using a timezone offset in seconds (for OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST bucketing)\",\"code\":\"```python\\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone, timedelta\\n\\ndef local_day_key(dt_unix, tz_offset_seconds):\\n    tz=timezone(timedelta(seconds=tz_offset_seconds))\\n    return datetime.fromtimestamp(dt_unix,tz=tz).date()\\n```\"},{\"description\":\"Aggregate a single local-day slice from OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST into min/max temp, condition set, and average wind\",\"code\":\"```python\\nentries=[e for e in forecast_data['list'] if e['dt_txt'].startswith(target_date)]\\ntemps=[e['main']['temp'] for e in entries]\\nwinds=[e['wind']['speed'] for e in entries]\\nconds=sorted({e['weather'][0]['main'] for e in entries})\\nsummary={'low':min(temps),'high':max(temps),'conditions':conds,'avg_wind':sum(winds)/len(winds)}\\n```\"}],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\",\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\"],\"toolkits\":[\"openweather_api\",\"weathermap\"],\"plan_id\":\"87d9a78537414941b4431dd451524c58\"},{\"index\":2,\"use_case\":\"search for latest AI developer tools and news for full-stack developers\",\"execution_guidance\":\"IMPORTANT: Follow the recommended plan below. Extract steps before execution, adapt to your current context, execute sequentially with current_step parameter, and check known pitfalls to avoid errors.\",\"recommended_plan_steps\":[\"[Required] [Prerequisite]: Define a few queries for security-focused developer tools plus recency window and timezone basis, then call COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS (iterate if too few results).\",\"[Required] [Step]: Parse COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS response.data (items may be under response.data.news_results), filter for relevance, dedupe by normalized link, and keep title, link, snippet, source, published_at.\",\"[Optional (if results are noisy/off-topic)] [Step]: Re-run COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS with stricter qualifiers or split into sub-queries by subtopic to improve precision.\",\"[Optional (if you need confirmation beyond snippets)] [Next Step]: Fetch a small set of top links using COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT, inspect response.data.statuses for per-URL failures, and extract minimal passages/metadata for “verified” notes.\",\"[Optional (if prioritization is unclear)] [Next Step]: Use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS (TIMESERIES) to compare candidate keywords before ordering items.\",\"[Required] [Fallback]: If COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS is empty or COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT has crawl errors, use COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB to find alternative accessible sources/pages, then retry and choose follow-ups from response.data.citations.\",\"[Required] [Step]: Draft a concise daily brief as bullets with clickable links, include published_at, and clearly mark verified (fetched) vs inferred items.\"],\"known_pitfalls\":[\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] response.data.has_results can be false with empty response.data.news_results when the recency window or query is too narrow.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS] Result nesting varies (e.g., items under response.data.news_results); hard-coded paths can drop valid items.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB] response.data.answer may be verbose; response.data.citations is the more reliable URL list for follow-ups.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Overall success can mask per-URL failures; check response.data.statuses for status='error' and tags like CRAWL_NOT_FOUND.\",\"[COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT] Low max_characters can truncate mid-JSON/text and cause parsing failures; retry with higher limits or skip the item.\"],\"reference_workbench_snippets\":[{\"description\":\"Parse a JSON object embedded within fetched text content\",\"code\":\"```python\\nimport json\\n\\ndef parse_embedded_json(text):\\n    a=text.find('{'); b=text.rfind('}')\\n    return json.loads(text[a:b+1]) if a>=0 and b>a else None\\n```\"}],\"difficulty\":\"easy\",\"primary_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\"],\"related_tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\"],\"toolkits\":[\"composio_search\"],\"plan_id\":\"1479ff0566a14a49a3eb7be66fd0c2b2\"}],\"toolkit_connection_statuses\":[{\"toolkit\":\"openweather_api\",\"description\":\"Provides access to current weather data, forecasts, and historical weather data for any location worldwide.\",\"has_active_connection\":false,\"status_message\":\"No Active connection for toolkit=openweather_api. You MUST call COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS (toolkit=\\\"openweather_api\\\") to create a connection BEFORE executing any openweather_api tools.\"},{\"toolkit\":\"weathermap\",\"description\":\"WeatherMap provides visual weather data, forecasts, and mappings, helping users understand climate patterns or track severe weather conditions\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"status_message\":\"This toolkit does not require authentication. Tools are ready to use.\"},{\"toolkit\":\"composio_search\",\"description\":\"Composio Search provides comprehensive web search across travel (flights, hotels, events), e-commerce (Amazon, Walmart, shopping), financial markets, news, academic research, images, and location services.\",\"has_active_connection\":true,\"status_message\":\"This toolkit does not require authentication. Tools are ready to use.\"}],\"tool_schemas\":{\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\":{\"toolkit\":\"WEATHERMAP\",\"tool_slug\":\"WEATHERMAP_WEATHER\",\"description\":\"Tool for querying the OpenWeatherMap API. Returns current weather conditions only — no UV index, AQI, or official alerts. Timestamps are in UTC; apply the timezone offset field before grouping by local day.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"location\"],\"properties\":{\"location\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"London,GB\",\"Redding,CA,US\",\"London\",\"New York\",\"Tokyo\"],\"description\":\"A real city name (e.g., 'London', 'New York', 'Tokyo'). MUST be an actual city name - NOT a placeholder like 'your location', 'current location', or 'my location'. City names must be in English/Latin characters only. You may optionally append a country code (e.g., 'London,GB'). For US cities with state abbreviations, use the 3-part format 'City,StateCode,US' (e.g., 'Redding,CA,US', 'Portland,OR,US') - the 2-part format 'City,StateCode' will be interpreted as a country code (e.g., 'CA' = Canada, not California). If a 'city not found' error occurs, retry with a simpler string (e.g., drop state code, use just 'City' or 'City,CountryCode'). Small or remote locations may return no data; handle gracefully rather than retrying indefinitely.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_NEWS\",\"description\":\"Search for the latest news articles and current events with smart filtering. Searches news-oriented sources only (not blogs, docs, or company pages). Results nest under `data.results.news_results`; a 200 response with empty `news_results` or `news_results_state: 'Fully empty'` means no results — broaden query or `when` window. Auto-correction (`showing_results_for`) can silently redirect queries; verify returned articles match intended topic. Only first page returned by default; follow `pagination.next` for more pages. Supports 100+ languages and countries. Use advanced operators like 'site:' for publisher filtering directly in your query. Examples: query=\\\"artificial intelligence\\\" + when=\\\"w\\\" for past week's AI news query=\\\"climate change\\\" + gl=\\\"us\\\" + hl=\\\"en\\\" for US climate news query=\\\"business news\\\" + when=\\\"d\\\" for today's business news query=\\\"site:bbc.com tesla\\\" + when=\\\"d\\\" for today's BBC Tesla news\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"properties\":{\"gl\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"us\",\"uk\",\"ca\",\"au\",\"de\",\"fr\",\"jp\",\"in\",\"br\",\"mx\"],\"description\":\"Country code for news region (ISO 3166-1 alpha-2). Determines which country's news sources to prioritize.\"},\"hl\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"en\",\"es\",\"fr\",\"de\",\"pt\",\"it\",\"ja\",\"ko\",\"zh-cn\",\"zh-tw\",\"ar\",\"hi\",\"ru\"],\"description\":\"Language code for news interface and results. Most languages use ISO 639-1 codes (e.g., 'en', 'es'). Chinese requires regional variants: 'zh-cn' (Simplified) or 'zh-tw' (Traditional). Standalone 'zh' is normalized to 'zh-cn'.\"},\"when\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"d\",\"w\",\"m\",\"y\"],\"description\":\"Time filter for news articles. 'd' = past day, 'w' = past week, 'm' = past month, 'y' = past year. These are coarse UTC-based buckets with no finer granularity; filter `published_at` client-side for precise ranges. Combining narrow queries with strict `when` filters frequently returns zero results; broaden either before concluding no data exists.\"},\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"artificial intelligence\",\"climate change\",\"site:bbc.com technology\",\"when:7d startup funding\",\"Tesla stock market\",\"COVID-19 vaccine news\"],\"description\":\"Search query for news articles. Supports advanced operators like 'site:', 'when:', etc. Cannot be used with topic_token, publication_token, or story_token.\"},\"start\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"minimum\":0,\"examples\":[0,10,20,30],\"description\":\"Result offset for pagination. Each page typically contains 10 results. Use multiples of 10 (0, 10, 20, 30, ...) to navigate pages. Stop paginating when a page returns no new results.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_FETCH_URL_CONTENT\",\"description\":\"Fetch and extract clean, readable page text (markdown) from public web pages (HTML content) using the Exa API. Use when you need to retrieve actual content from search results or documentation links to extract setup steps, requirements, or citations. Only works with web page URLs - does not support direct links to images, PDFs, or other binary files.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"urls\"],\"properties\":{\"text\":{\"type\":\"boolean\",\"default\":true,\"description\":\"Include extracted markdown text content from the page. Defaults to true.\"},\"urls\":{\"type\":\"array\",\"items\":{\"type\":\"string\"},\"examples\":[[\"https://example.com/article\",\"https://docs.python.org/\"]],\"description\":\"List of public URLs to web pages (HTML content) to fetch content from. URLs must be valid and publicly accessible. Do not use direct links to images (.jpg, .png, .gif), PDFs, or other binary files - use web page URLs only. Also accepts a single URL string.\"},\"extras\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"description\":\"Additional content options like imageLinks or links counts (e.g., {'imageLinks': 3, 'links': 5}).\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"integer\"}},\"summary\":{\"anyOf\":[{\"type\":\"boolean\"},{\"type\":\"object\",\"additionalProperties\":{\"type\":\"string\"}}],\"description\":\"Include AI-generated summary of the page content. Can be boolean or object with query/schema options.\"},\"max_characters\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"description\":\"Maximum number of characters to extract from each page. Maps to text.maxCharacters in Exa API.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\":{\"toolkit\":\"WEATHERMAP\",\"tool_slug\":\"WEATHERMAP_GEOCODE_LOCATION\",\"description\":\"Tool to resolve a human place name into canonical lat/lon coordinates using OpenWeather Geocoding API. Use when you need to convert location strings (city names, addresses) into coordinates for weather forecasts or other location-based queries. Returns up to 5 candidate matches; the first result is typically the most relevant.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"q\"],\"properties\":{\"q\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"Rarotonga,CK\",\"London,GB\",\"Austin,TX,US\",\"New York\",\"Tokyo,JP\"],\"description\":\"Location query string in format 'city' or 'city,country_code' or 'city,state,country_code'. For US locations, you can include state code (e.g., 'Austin,TX,US'). Use ISO 3166 country codes (e.g., 'London,GB', 'Paris,FR'). The API supports 200,000+ registered locations.\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":5,\"maximum\":5,\"minimum\":1,\"examples\":[1,3,5],\"description\":\"Maximum number of location matches to return (1-5). Use this to limit results when multiple locations share the same name. Default is 5.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_GEOCODING_DIRECT\",\"description\":\"Tool to convert a location name into geographic coordinates. Use when you need latitude and longitude for a given location after confirming the precise name.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"q\"],\"properties\":{\"q\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"London,UK\"],\"description\":\"Location query including city name, state code and country code separated by commas (e.g., 'London,UK'). Ambiguous queries can return multiple mismatched locations; use the full three-part format 'city,state_code,country_code' (e.g., 'Springfield,IL,US') and verify the returned country/region before using coordinates downstream.\"},\"limit\":{\"type\":\"integer\",\"default\":5,\"maximum\":5,\"minimum\":1,\"examples\":[5],\"description\":\"Number of results to return (1 to 5). Defaults to 5. Use 1 only for unambiguous locations; for ambiguous queries review all returned results to select the correct match.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_WEB\",\"description\":\"Perform a web search using the Exa API. Returns a nested structure: narrative summary under results.answer, sources under results.citations (and optionally results.organic_results). Prioritize results.citations as primary evidence over results.answer, which can be vague. Only indexes publicly available content — no paywalled, login-gated, or private content. No date filters enforced; include recency terms in query and verify dates in snippets manually. Throttle to ~1–2 requests/second; bursty queries trigger HTTP 429. Large responses may be stored remotely — use structure_info to locate results.answer and results.citations.\",\"input_schema\":{\"type\":\"object\",\"required\":[\"query\"],\"properties\":{\"query\":{\"type\":\"string\",\"examples\":[\"Coffee\"],\"description\":\"The search query for the Composio Exa API. Must be non-empty; using any other parameter name (e.g., 'q') causes an invalid-request error. Include qualifiers (year, region, platform, intent) for better results — broad queries return generic content; excessive site: or quoted-term filters can return zero results. Add disambiguating terms (city, role, domain) when searching for people or organizations with common names.\"}}},\"hasFullSchema\":true},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\",\"description\":\"Tool to retrieve current weather data for a location. Use when you need up-to-the-minute weather inf...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET_CURRENT_WEATHER\"]}}},\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\":{\"toolkit\":\"OPENWEATHER_API\",\"tool_slug\":\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\",\"description\":\"Tool to get a 5-day forecast every 3 hours (up to 40 UTC timestamps). Exactly one location identifie...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"OPENWEATHER_API_GET5_DAY_FORECAST\"]}}},\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\":{\"toolkit\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH\",\"tool_slug\":\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\",\"description\":\"Discover trending topics, search patterns, and popularity data. Analyzes search interest over time, ...\",\"hasFullSchema\":false,\"schemaRef\":{\"tool\":\"COMPOSIO_GET_TOOL_SCHEMAS\",\"args\":{\"tool_slugs\":[\"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TRENDS\"]}}}},\"time_info\":{\"current_time_utc\":\"2026-06-22T16:00:17.817Z\",\"current_time_utc_epoch_seconds\":1782144017,\"message\":\"\\n          - This is time in UTC timezone. Get timezone from user if you needed.\\n          - Always use this time info to construct parameters for tool calls appropriately even when the tool call requires relative times like 'last week', 'last 24 hours', 'today', 'tomorrow' etc.\\n          - Do not hallucinate the time or timezone by yourself.\\n        \"},\"session\":{\"id\":\"girl\",\"generate_id\":true,\"instructions\":\"REQUIRED: Pass session_id \\\"girl\\\" in ALL subsequent meta tool calls for this workflow.\"},\"next_steps_guidance\":[\"1) You may call COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS: Some toolkits lack active connections\",\"2) Extract validated plan steps returned above, acknowledge each step, then execute sequentially updating current_step parameter. Check pitfalls during execution.\"],\"success\":true,\"error\":null},\"error\":null,\"log_id\":\"log_dQBc1R25he8_\",\"successful\":true}"}],"details":{"mcpServer":"composio","mcpTool":"COMPOSIO_SEARCH_TOOLS"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782144017922}}
{"type":"message","id":"5cfc67a3","parentId":"1284119f","timestamp":"2026-06-22T16:00:22.059Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Ahora necesito conectar OpenWeather API para obtener el clima y luego buscar noticias técnicas de IA. Primero voy a conectar OpenWeather:\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"a23dca920e3b4fe0b943786711ab8621","name":"composio__COMPOSIO_MANAGE_CONNECTIONS","arguments":{"session_id":"girl","toolkits":[{"name":"openweather_api","action":"add","alias":"weather"}]},"partialArgs":"{\"session_id\": \"girl\", \"toolkits\": [{\"name\": \"openweather_api\", \"action\": \"add\", \"alias\": \"weather\"}]}"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"litellm","model":"online/openrouter/deepseek/deepseek-v3.2","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782144017930,"responseId":"gen-1782144018-7KlhlVHGanu1fqjIXfLo"}}
